        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-03-01 02:07:45.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI don't think we should add this change.   This falls under the \"selfSignedCertificates\" which itself is used for non-production environments, chances are that the hostname in the self signed cert has not been crafted properly.   Since this may impose testing restrictions in some environments.  Note that hostname validation is properly done in certs by default (else statement), so this option only comes into play when somebody explicitly marks the client to support remove self signed certs.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
